Hi all,

     A quick introduction from me, as well. I am an Assistant Professor 
at the University of Hannover and mainly working with my group in 
wide-area virtual network provisioning, SDN, and network processing.

With respect to gaia, in collaboration with Arjuna, Jon, and other 
colleagues, I have been working on Virtual Public Networks, i.e., 
virtual networks dynamically provisioned to exploit the unused capacity 
in home broadband networks. I am particularly interested in outsourcing 
the management and configuration of such networks to third parties using 
SDN.

I'm very glad to see a forum where we can share our views on global 
Internet access.

- Panagiotis


