      <pre wrap="">Hmmm.  This email is going to get rather long if we all keep adding to it, but I'll attach one more.  I'm Scott Burleigh, a principal engineer at NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory, which is operated by the California Institute of Technology.  I've been working on "delay-tolerant networking" technologies since 1998.  While the original motivation for the DTN research was to address issues in space flight mission operations, it has become clear that the capabilities of DTN can be applied to problems in terrestrial communications as well, particularly communications serving populations for whom Internet access may be elusive due to geographic, economic, or even political obstacles.  I'm interested in solving those problems.

Scott

