Hi all,

My name is Nishanth Sastry. I am a Lecturer (~asst. prof.) at King's Colleg=
e London, where I have been working on content consumption and content deli=
very in various contexts, ranging from social media and user-generated cont=
ent to over-the-top TV streaming. I am interested both in large-scale measu=
rements as well as architectural improvements/innovations. I am also intere=
sted in design for development outside of networking as well (e.g. https://=
sites.google.com/site/cellcentives/ was an old effort).

Within this forum, I'd be interested in:

a) (from a measurements perspective) understanding and characterising curre=
nt use cases and needs, esp. for content delivery, in wider cultural contex=
ts than we have been traditionally looking at.
b) helping address architecture challenges, e.g., cost constraints. I parti=
cularly enjoy simple solutions that repurpose existing technology to save c=
osts (e.g., prev. efforts include citywide wifi at near zero cost by secure=
ly reusing private wifi APs, and repurposing TV broadcast to decrease netwo=
rk footprint of TV streaming).

I am in this forum because:
- I like the idea of free/low-cost connectivity for all, and because I beli=
eve getting this right could perhaps be the most significant contribution t=
hat we can make as network architects.
- In contrast to the 'real' Internet, this could be a neat research playgro=
und for actually testing/deploying some recent novel architectural ideas (i=
ncluding DTN/ICN, which I have dabbled in a bit), and if we're lucky, havin=
g those ideas be used by real people, at scale.
- Also, I kinda like the sense of belonging - being part of mother gaia, as=
 it were ;)

cheers
Nishanth
