Hi all,&nbsp;
<div><br>
</div>
<div>
<div>My name is Nishanth Sastry. I am a Lecturer (~asst. prof.) at King's C=
ollege London, where I have been working on content consumption and content=
 delivery in various contexts, ranging from social media and user-generated=
 content to over-the-top TV streaming.
 I am interested both in large-scale measurements as well as architectural =
improvements/innovations. I am also interested in design for development ou=
tside of networking as well (e.g.
<a href=3D"https://sites.google.com/site/cellcentives/">https://sites.googl=
e.com/site/cellcentives/</a> was an old effort).</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>
<div>Within this forum, I'd be interested in:</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>a) (from a measurements perspective) understanding and characterising =
current use cases and needs, esp. for content delivery, in wider cultural c=
ontexts than we have been traditionally looking at.</div>
<div>b) helping address architecture challenges, e.g., cost constraints. I =
particularly enjoy simple solutions that repurpose existing technology to s=
ave costs (e.g., prev. efforts include citywide wifi at near zero cost by s=
ecurely reusing private wifi APs,
 and repurposing TV broadcast to decrease network footprint of TV streaming=
).&nbsp;</div>
</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>I am in this forum because:</div>
<div>- I like the idea of free/low-cost connectivity for all, and because I=
 believe getting this right could perhaps be the most significant contribut=
ion that we can make as network architects.&nbsp;</div>
<div>- In contrast to the 'real' Internet, this could be a neat research pl=
ayground for actually testing/deploying some recent novel architectural ide=
as (including DTN/ICN, which I have dabbled in a bit), and if we're lucky, =
having those ideas be used by real
 people, at scale.&nbsp;</div>
<div>- Also, I kinda like the sense of belonging - being part of mother gai=
a, as it were ;)&nbsp;</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>cheers</div>
<div>Nishanth</div>
