Nice to meet those of you I don't already know...

I wear two hats in this context:  I lead the Tier group at Berkeley, which
is among oldest groups working in this space (at least among universities),
and I am an advisor to Google's efforts in the access area (and a Google
VP).

Tier worked on DTN for developing regions via Kevin Fall, as well as
long-distance WiFi, power systems for remote networking, and our latest
work, which is on low-cost GSM solutions for rural areas based on software
radios.

Google has various projects in the access space including shared fiber,
wireless access via balloons, TV white spaces, and of course heavy
influence on Android.

-Eric



