Greetings.

I'm Nick Feamster, professor at Georgia Tech.  I come to this group =
having worked with Arjuna on the deployment of our BISmark home network =
testbed as part of the PAWS project at Cambridge (access to low-income =
communities).  We also have quite a lot of deployments in both wireline =
(home gateway) and cellular (Android app) in many developing countries.  =
  We are working on additional deployments in developing countries to =
measure access network performance in this places.  A view or our =
current deployment is available here: http://networkdashboard.org/

I've also done lots of work in anti-censorship and universal access, =
ranging from both the design of circumvention systems to measurement of =
censorship and information manipulation.

Thanks,
Nick

