I'm Vint Cerf. Many years ago, my colleague, Bob Kahn, and I did the
initial design of the Internet. I have spent 4 decades working in various
capacities to extend its reach and functionality (along with a lot of other
people!). At Google, I am VP and chief Internet evangelist, so I can
resonate with getting another 4 billion people on line. I was part of the
team that did the original design of DTN at JPL and continue to work in
that space with a growing team. I wear a lot of other hats but I won't bore
you with recounting them hear - many have to do with various aspects of
Internet technology and governance. I am very interested in the work of the
gaia team.

v

