Hi guys

I'm Jon and I'm currently Head of User Research for Digital Inclusion
- at GDS (Government Digital Services) within the UK Government
(although strictly it should read non-user research).  My background
has been a strong mix of academic and industrial research around
people interacting with each other, technology and environments (so
psychology, human-computer interaction etc). Some of which has had
focus on socially excluded individuals/groups, but lots of other
things too over the past 20 years.

My focus at the moment is on the delivery of the UK's Digital
Inclusion Strategy paying particular attention to individuals, small &
medium sized business as well as 3rd sector organisations. In the UK
we have 21% of the adult population that lack basic digital literacy
skills and 14% that are completely off line. I'm trying to make sure
folk here don't lose sight of that when carrying out various projects.
(I'm also looking at other countries too, not just the UK).

So, I'm always keen to learn and experiment, and glad to promote
projects and disseminate knowledge - really looking forward to
participating in this forum.

Nice to meet you!

Jon


