Greetings,

I'm a researcher at IBM Research, Dublin. Officially I'm a part of the Big
Data team, wherein my primary focus is batch-processing and
stream-processing systems, but I indulge in "ICT4D-centric things" on the
sides. My recent ICT4D work has included an analysis of Internet
censorship in Pakistan and a low-cost video conferencing solution that
leverages Raspberry Pi for the developing world. I'm currently interested
in using Raspberry Pi for other functions, such as Internet security, in
the developing world.

Best,
Zubair

